  "text": "A total of 41 cases of rhino-orbital mucormycosis ( ) or ROCM ( ) were identified n p 21 n p 20 (table 1) . One patient with ROCM also had pulmonary mucormycosis, and 1 patient each with rhino-orbital mucormycosis had coexisting cutaneous and pulmonary disease. All patients had mucormycosis proven by histopathologic examination of a biopsy specimen, in accordance with Mycosis Study Group-European Organization for the Research and Treatment of Cancer criteria [CITATION_1] .",
